Copulatory organ as in diagnosis (
Figs 72–89
). Epigynal field wider than long, with bilobate to trilobate anterior margin and short, sometimes indistinct or reduced anterior bands. LL with bands of muscle sigilla in their lateral parts. First winding wide, converging slightly posteriorly. Fertilisation duct moderately long, narrow, laterad in ventral view.
